messages.msgSnippet: Paul- I think we care for Hakama the same way now as then. Fold them up after use and press them in hot or cold water, hang dry with the creases in place all
messages.messageBody:
Paul-
I think we care for Hakama the same way now as then. Fold them up after
use and press them in hot or cold water, hang dry with the creases in place
all along.
I have also heard that one placed them under your futon where body heat
would do the job of "ironing"

Tom

Hi All

I was windering while I was washing and ironing the
other day...

Did the Japanese in fuedal times have irons.

If not how did they manage to get there kimono hakama
etc pressed, and those cresses in the hakama etc in
place.

After all silk always looks creased to death when it
dries.

Paul
